function clean_column(col::AbstractString)
    return replace(lowercase(strip(col)), r"[\s-]+" => "_")
end
```

The `clean_column` function accepts a string, which is the name of the column. It lowercases the string using the `lowercase` function, then removes any leading or trailing whitespaces using the `strip` function. Finally, it uses the `replace` function to replace any occurrences of spaces or hyphens with underscores, using a regular expression (`r"[\s-]+"`) to match one or more spaces or hyphens. The result is the cleaned column name.
